            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle t_{i}=(\alpha -1)w_{i}}
  .  In this case, the optimal solution could contain at most 
  
    
      
        α
        −
        1
      
    
    {\displaystyle \alpha -1}
   copies of 
  
    
      
        i
      
    
    {\displaystyle i}
  .
Multiple dominance
The 
  
    
      
        i
      
    
    {\displaystyle i}
  -th item is  multiply dominated by a single item 
  
    
      
        j
      
    
    {\displaystyle j}
  , written as 
  
    
      
        i
        
          ≪
          
            m
          
        
